# Research-Wiki EOL policy.
#
# Research-Wiki ships immutable, hash-verified KB export packs: every file
# inside `literature-kb/06_Exports/<pack>/` has its SHA-256 recorded in the
# sibling `export_manifest.json`, and `lgrlw lint` rejects the whole project
# if any byte has changed since the pack was written.
#
# Strategy: force LF everywhere -- including working trees on Windows.
# Combined with the `newline="\n"` guards in every `write_text` call under
# `src/lgrlw/` (see fs.py::write_frontmatter for the rationale), this makes
# export pack bytes identical across every OS after a git round trip, so
# the manifest's SHA-256 digests survive check-out on ubuntu-latest and
# windows-latest alike.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit text file kinds (all LF). Keep these *after* the `* text=auto`
# line above so later attributes win.
*.py      text eol=lf
*.md      text eol=lf
*.yml     text eol=lf
*.yaml    text eol=lf
*.toml    text eol=lf
*.json    text eol=lf
*.bib     text eol=lf

# Binary assets (extend as needed).
*.png     binary
*.jpg     binary
*.pdf     binary
*.ico     binary
